<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>HYMN FOR LAUDS OF ADVENT UNTIL 16 DECEMBER</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                     G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  A voice resounds from heaven,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    it echoes in the night;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    let dreams and anguish flee,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the light of Christ shines forth.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  The heart awakes from slumber
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    no longer troubled by evil;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    a new star is shining 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    in the darkness of the world.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  Behold the Lamb of God,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the price of our ransom;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    with living faith we implore
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    his forgiveness and peace.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  When at the end of time 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    Christ comes in his glory,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    may his grace release us
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    from his fearsome judgement.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  Praise be to Christ the Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to the Father and the Spirit,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    as it was in the beginning,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                      Am      G Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    is now and ever shall be. Amen.
</PRE></H3>
